# 8. 受け継ぐハート

Minori: Huff... Huff...
MEIKO: You're starting to slow down, Minori! Keep swinging your arms!
Minori: O-Okay...!
MEIKO: You need to relax your upper body more, Shizuku! Try to stay loose!
Shizuku: Okay...!
MEIKO: Nice work! Three more laps to go!
Airi: Did you just add more?!
KAITO: Haha. MEIKO makes for a tough drill sergeant...
Rin: You can do it, girls! Go, go, MORE MORE JUMP♪
Airi: For today's talk-show lesson, I'm going to have you come up with funny one-liners on the spot to improve your thinking speed and cleverness.
Airi: So, here's your first question! “In a previous life, this cat was an idol! How could you tell?”
Minori: What?! U-Uhh...
Minori: I know! Because it's really cute!
Airi: Hmm... Speed and confidence are important, but that's a bit of a weak response since cats are cute to begin with.
Shizuku: Umm... What if it's because it kneads in a rhythmical manner?
Airi: O-Oh no... My heart's melting just imagining that...
Airi: 98, 99... 100!
Airi: *Sigh* (That was rough...)
Airi: (Leave it to Haruka to come up with a tough workout. Having planks at the end really embodies her work ethic.)
Airi: (Wait, huh?!)
Haruka: 121, 122...
Airi: (She has her right arm and left leg raised...? And she's not even out of breath.)
Airi: (Alright, I'm also gonna raise the bar and give it another go...!)
Airi: Phew... Another exhausting day...
Airi: (But it definitely feels like I've come a long way.)
Airi: (I've gotta maintain this momentum and keep doing everything I can.)
Airi: (Before I go to bed, I'll stretch, put together another talk-show lesson plan and... Oh, I should take a look at that idol program I recorded.)
Airi: (This episode was supposed to involve following a popular idol around...)
Airi: Oh...
Airi: (Come to think of it, do I still have the recording of that episode of Close-up Professional...?)
Airi: Let's see... I wanna say the DVD Mom burned for me was... Oh, here it is!
Airi: It's pretty old... I hope it still plays.
Hiyori: <One, two, three, four...!>
Airi: Yes, it still works.
Hiyori: <Okay, that felt pretty good! I should do another run while it's still fresh in my head...>
Airi: (Hiyori really is an amazing person... She's always shining so bright.)
Airi: (Just watching her fills me with encouragement!)
Hiyori: <My goal is to put smiles on the faces of those who are watching me.>
Hiyori: <I want them to look forward to giving the next day their very best.>
Hiyori: <I think that's why I'm able to maintain my optimism like this.>
Airi: Oh...
Airi: (That's right. Those were the words that made me...)
Camera Operator: <That motto suits you very well, Hiyori.>
Hiyori: <Thank you! But it's actually another person's words.>
Airi: What?
Hiyori: <A legendary idol whom I admire very much...>
Hiyori: <They're the words of Hinako Arisawa.>
Airi: ...!
Airi: Ms. Arisawa said that...?
Airi: I had no idea...
Arisawa: That is why I think true idols are those who can spread hope simply by being who they are.
Arisawa: And most importantly, they must have hearts full of persistent optimism. That is my solemn belief.
Airi: (That explains why I...)
Airi: (I have to do my absolute best...)
Airi: (I need to put all my heart into creating an unwavering beacon.)
Airi: (To spread hope to as many people as I can.)
Airi: So, I'll give the Lumina Grand Prix everything I've got!
